
[1]anamorphosis

   ANAMORPHOSIS, n. [Gr. formation.]

   In perspective drawings, a deformed or distorted portrait or figure,
   which, in one point of view, is confused or unintelligible, and in
   another, is an exact and regular representation; or confused to the
   naked eye, but reflected from a plain or curved mirror, appearing
   regular, and in right proportion.
